INDRA JATRA, also known as YenyÄ, is the biggest religious street festival in Kathmandu, Nepal. The celebrations consist of two events, INDRA JATRA AND Kumari Jatra. INDRA JATRA is marked by masked dances of deities and demons, displays of sacred images and tableaus in honor of the deity Indra, the king of heaven. In 2017, the Yenya or Indra Jatra committee set aside a day for women to drink from Hatu Dyaa (Swet Bhairab) an activity which in the past had not been segregated by gender, and was therefore accessible mostly to men. âœ… Follow / ğŸ“¸ Video Credit : : @karmesh_shrestha ğŸ“ŒFollow us @roamingaroundnepal for beautiful Nepal.
